{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm going to try and explain why it is that perhaps"},{"time":4000,"text":"we don't understand as much as we think we do."},{"time":6000,"text":"I'd like to begin with four questions."},{"time":9000,"text":"This is not some sort of cultural thing for the time of year."},{"time":12000,"text":"That's an in-joke, by the way."},{"time":14000,"text":"But these four questions, actually,"},{"time":17000,"text":"are ones that people who even know quite a lot about science find quite hard."},{"time":20000,"text":"And they're questions that I've asked of science television producers,"},{"time":25000,"text":"of audiences of science educators --"},{"time":28000,"text":"so that's science teachers -- and also of seven-year-olds,"},{"time":32000,"text":"and I find that the seven-year-olds do marginally better"},{"time":35000,"text":"than the other audiences, which is somewhat surprising."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37000,"text":"So the first question, and you might want to write this down,"},{"time":40000,"text":"either on a bit of paper, physically, or a virtual piece of paper"},{"time":44000,"text":"in your head. And, for viewers at home, you can try this as well."},{"time":47000,"text":"A little seed weighs next to nothing and a tree weighs a lot, right?"},{"time":52000,"text":"I think we agree on that. Where does the tree get the stuff that makes up this chair,"},{"time":58000,"text":"right? Where does all this stuff come from?"},{"time":61000,"text":"(Knocks)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":62000,"text":"And your next question is, can you light a little torch-bulb"},{"time":68000,"text":"with a battery, a bulb and one piece of wire?"},{"time":73000,"text":"And would you be able to, kind of, draw a -- you don't have to draw"},{"time":75000,"text":"the diagram, but would you be able to draw the diagram,"},{"time":77000,"text":"if you had to do it? Or would you just say,"},{"time":79000,"text":"that's actually not possible?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":82000,"text":"The third question is, why is it hotter in summer than in winter?"},{"time":86000,"text":"I think we can probably agree that it is hotter in summer than in winter,"},{"time":91000,"text":"but why? And finally, would you be able to --"},{"time":97000,"text":"and you can sort of scribble it, if you like --"},{"time":99000,"text":"scribble a plan diagram of the solar system,"},{"time":102000,"text":"showing the shape of the planets' orbits?"},{"time":106000,"text":"Would you be able to do that?"},{"time":107000,"text":"And if you can, just scribble a pattern."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112000,"text":"OK. Now, children get their ideas not from teachers,"},{"time":118000,"text":"as teachers often think, but actually from common sense,"},{"time":121000,"text":"from experience of the world around them,"},{"time":123000,"text":"from all the things that go on between them and their peers,"},{"time":127000,"text":"and their carers, and their parents, and all of that. Experience."},{"time":132000,"text":"And one of the great experts in this field, of course, was, bless him,"},{"time":137000,"text":"Cardinal Wolsey. Be very careful what you get into people's heads"},{"time":141000,"text":"because it's virtually impossible to shift it afterwards, right?"},{"time":144000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":147000,"text":"I'm not quite sure how he died, actually."},{"time":149000,"text":"Was he beheaded in the end, or hung?"},{"time":151000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":152000,"text":"Now, those questions, which, of course, you've got right,"},{"time":154000,"text":"and you haven't been conferring, and so on."},{"time":156000,"text":"And I -- you know, normally, I would pick people out and humiliate,"},{"time":159000,"text":"but maybe not in this instance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161000,"text":"A little seed weighs a lot and, basically, all this stuff,"},{"time":165000,"text":"99 percent of this stuff, came out of the air."},{"time":168000,"text":"Now, I guarantee that about 85 percent of you, or maybe it's fewer at TED,"},{"time":172000,"text":"will have said it comes out of the ground. And some people,"},{"time":175000,"text":"probably two of you, will come up and argue with me afterwards,"},{"time":178000,"text":"and say that actually, it comes out of the ground."},{"time":180000,"text":"Now, if that was true, we'd have trucks going round the country,"},{"time":182000,"text":"filling people's gardens in with soil, it'd be a fantastic business."},{"time":185000,"text":"But, actually, we don't do that."},{"time":187000,"text":"The mass of this comes out of the air."},{"time":190000,"text":"Now, I passed all my biology exams in Britain."},{"time":194000,"text":"I passed them really well, but I still came out of school"},{"time":196000,"text":"thinking that that stuff came out of the ground."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199000,"text":"Second one: can you light a little torch-bulb with a battery bulb and one piece of wire?"},{"time":203000,"text":"Yes, you can, and I'll show you in a second how to do that."},{"time":205000,"text":"Now, I have some rather bad news,"},{"time":207000,"text":"which is that I had a piece of video that I was about to show you,"},{"time":210000,"text":"which unfortunately -- the sound doesn't work in this room,"},{"time":213000,"text":"so I'm going to describe to you, in true \"Monty Python\" fashion,"},{"time":216000,"text":"what happens in the video. And in the video, a group of researchers"},{"time":221000,"text":"go to MIT on graduation day."},{"time":223000,"text":"We chose MIT because, obviously, that's a very long way away"},{"time":226000,"text":"from here, and you wouldn't mind too much,"},{"time":228000,"text":"but it sort of works the same way in Britain"},{"time":231000,"text":"and in the West Coast of the USA."},{"time":233000,"text":"And we asked them these questions, and we asked those questions"},{"time":237000,"text":"of science graduates, and they couldn't answer them."},{"time":239000,"text":"And so, there's a whole lot of people saying,"},{"time":241000,"text":"\"I'd be very surprised if you told me that this came out of the air."},{"time":243000,"text":"That's very surprising to me.\" And those are science graduates."},{"time":247000,"text":"And we intercut it with, \"We are the premier science university in the world,\""},{"time":250000,"text":"because of British-like hubris."},{"time":252000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":253000,"text":"And when we gave graduate engineers that question,"},{"time":256000,"text":"they said it couldn't be done."},{"time":258000,"text":"And when we gave them a battery, and a piece of wire, and a bulb,"},{"time":262000,"text":"and said, \"Can you do it?\" They couldn't do it. Right?"},{"time":266000,"text":"And that's no different from Imperial College in London, by the way,"},{"time":269000,"text":"it's not some sort of anti-American thing going on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273000,"text":"As if. Now, the reason this matters is we pay lots and lots of money"},{"time":279000,"text":"for teaching people -- we might as well get it right."},{"time":281000,"text":"And there are also some societal reasons"},{"time":283000,"text":"why we might want people to understand what it is that's happening"},{"time":287000,"text":"in photosynthesis. For example, one half of the carbon equation"},{"time":290000,"text":"is how much we emit, and the other half of the carbon equation,"},{"time":293000,"text":"as I'm very conscious as a trustee of Kew,"},{"time":295000,"text":"is how much things soak up, and they soak up carbon dioxide out of the atmosphere."},{"time":300000,"text":"That's what plants actually do for a living."},{"time":303000,"text":"And, for any Finnish people in the audience, this is a Finnish pun:"},{"time":306000,"text":"we are, both literally and metaphorically, skating on thin ice"},{"time":311000,"text":"if we don't understand that kind of thing."},{"time":314000,"text":"Now, here's how you do the battery and the bulb."},{"time":316000,"text":"It's so easy, isn't it? Of course, you all knew that."},{"time":320000,"text":"But if you haven't played with a battery and a bulb,"},{"time":322000,"text":"if you've only seen a circuit diagram,"},{"time":324000,"text":"you might not be able to do that, and that's one of the problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328000,"text":"So, why is it hotter in summer than in winter?"},{"time":330000,"text":"We learn, as children, that you get closer to something that's hot,"},{"time":333000,"text":"and it burns you. It's a very powerful bit of learning,"},{"time":336000,"text":"and it happens pretty early on."},{"time":338000,"text":"By extension, we think to ourselves, \"Why it's hotter in summer than in winter"},{"time":341000,"text":"must be because we're closer to the Sun.\""},{"time":344000,"text":"I promise you that most of you will have got that."},{"time":346000,"text":"Oh, you're all shaking your heads,"},{"time":347000,"text":"but only a few of you are shaking your heads very firmly."},{"time":350000,"text":"Other ones are kind of going like this. All right."},{"time":352000,"text":"It's hotter in summer than in winter because the rays from the Sun"},{"time":355000,"text":"are spread out more, right, because of the tilt of the Earth."},{"time":359000,"text":"And if you think the tilt is tilting us closer, no, it isn't."},{"time":362000,"text":"The Sun is 93 million miles away, and we're tilting like this, right?"},{"time":366000,"text":"It makes no odds. In fact, in the Northern Hemisphere,"},{"time":369000,"text":"we're further from the Sun in summer,"},{"time":372000,"text":"as it happens, but it makes no odds, the difference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375000,"text":"OK, now, the scribble of the diagram of the solar system."},{"time":378000,"text":"If you believe, as most of you probably do,"},{"time":380000,"text":"that it's hotter in summer than in winter because we're closer to the Sun,"},{"time":382000,"text":"you must have drawn an ellipse."},{"time":384000,"text":"Right? That would explain it, right?"},{"time":386000,"text":"Except, in your -- you're nodding -- now, in your ellipse,"},{"time":390000,"text":"have you thought, \"Well, what happens during the night?\""},{"time":392000,"text":"Between Australia and here, right, they've got summer"},{"time":396000,"text":"and we've got winter, and what --"},{"time":399000,"text":"does the Earth kind of rush towards the Sun at night,"},{"time":402000,"text":"and then rush back again? I mean, it's a very strange thing going on,"},{"time":405000,"text":"and we hold these two models in our head, of what's right and what isn't right,"},{"time":409000,"text":"and we do that, as human beings, in all sorts of fields."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413000,"text":"So, here's Copernicus' view of what the solar system looked like as a plan."},{"time":418000,"text":"That's pretty much what you should have on your piece of paper. Right?"},{"time":421000,"text":"And this is NASA's view. They're stunningly similar."},{"time":424000,"text":"I hope you notice the coincidence here."},{"time":427000,"text":"What would you do if you knew that people had this misconception,"},{"time":431000,"text":"right, in their heads, of elliptical orbits"},{"time":434000,"text":"caused by our experiences as children?"},{"time":436000,"text":"What sort of diagram would you show them of the solar system,"},{"time":438000,"text":"to show that it's not really like that?"},{"time":440000,"text":"You'd show them something like this, wouldn't you?"},{"time":442000,"text":"It's a plan, looking down from above."},{"time":443000,"text":"But, no, look what I found in the textbooks."},{"time":446000,"text":"That's what you show people, right? These are from textbooks,"},{"time":449000,"text":"from websites, educational websites --"},{"time":451000,"text":"and almost anything you pick up is like that."},{"time":453000,"text":"And the reason it's like that is because it's dead boring"},{"time":455000,"text":"to have a load of concentric circles,"},{"time":457000,"text":"whereas that's much more exciting, to look at something at that angle,"},{"time":460000,"text":"isn't it? Right? And by doing it at that angle,"},{"time":463000,"text":"if you've got that misconception in your head, then that"},{"time":465000,"text":"two-dimensional representation of a three-dimensional thing will be ellipses."},{"time":470000,"text":"So you've -- it's crap, isn't it really? As we say."},{"time":474000,"text":"So, these mental models -- we look for evidence that reinforces our models."},{"time":477000,"text":"We do this, of course, with matters of race, and politics, and everything else,"},{"time":481000,"text":"and we do it in science as well. So we look, just look --"},{"time":483000,"text":"and scientists do it, constantly -- we look for evidence"},{"time":486000,"text":"that reinforces our models, and some folks are just all too able"},{"time":489000,"text":"and willing to provide the evidence that reinforces the models."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492000,"text":"So, being I'm in the United States, I'll have a dig at the Europeans."},{"time":496000,"text":"These are examples of what I would say is bad practice in science"},{"time":499000,"text":"teaching centers. These pictures are from La Villette in France"},{"time":502000,"text":"and the welcome wing of the Science Museum in London."},{"time":506000,"text":"And, if you look at the, kind of the way these things are constructed,"},{"time":510000,"text":"there's a lot of mediation by glass, and it's very blue, and kind of professional --"},{"time":515000,"text":"in that way that, you know, Woody Allen comes up"},{"time":518000,"text":"from under the sheets in that scene in \"Annie Hall,\""},{"time":520000,"text":"and said, \"God, that's so professional.\" And that you don't --"},{"time":523000,"text":"there's no passion in it, and it's not hands on, right,"},{"time":526000,"text":"and, you know, pun intended. Whereas good interpretation --"},{"time":529000,"text":"I'll use an example from nearby -- is San Francisco Exploratorium,"},{"time":533000,"text":"where all the things that -- the demonstrations, and so on,"},{"time":536000,"text":"are made out of everyday objects that children can understand,"},{"time":539000,"text":"it's very hands-on, and they can engage with, and experiment with."},{"time":542000,"text":"And I know that if the graduates at MIT"},{"time":544000,"text":"and in the Imperial College in London had had the battery and the wire"},{"time":548000,"text":"and the bit of stuff, and you know, been able to do it,"},{"time":551000,"text":"they would have learned how it actually works,"},{"time":554000,"text":"rather than thinking that they follow circuit diagrams and can't do it."},{"time":558000,"text":"So good interpretation is more about"},{"time":560000,"text":"things that are bodged and stuffed and of my world, right?"},{"time":564000,"text":"And things that -- where there isn't an extra barrier"},{"time":566000,"text":"of a piece of glass or machined titanium,"},{"time":569000,"text":"and it all looks fantastic, OK?"},{"time":571000,"text":"And the Exploratorium does that really, really well."},{"time":574000,"text":"And it's amateur, but amateur in the best sense,"},{"time":577000,"text":"in other words, the root of the word being of love and passion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":582000,"text":"So, children are not empty vessels, OK?"},{"time":584000,"text":"So, as \"Monty Python\" would have it,"},{"time":586000,"text":"this is a bit Lord Privy Seal to say so,"},{"time":588000,"text":"but this is -- children are not empty vessels."},{"time":590000,"text":"They come with their own ideas and their own theories,"},{"time":592000,"text":"and unless you work with those, then you won't be able to shift them,"},{"time":596000,"text":"right? And I probably haven't shifted your ideas"},{"time":598000,"text":"of how the world and universe operates, either."},{"time":601000,"text":"But this applies, equally, to matters of trying to sell new technology."},{"time":604000,"text":"For example, we are, in Britain, we're trying to do a digital switchover"},{"time":607000,"text":"of the whole population into digital technology [for television]."},{"time":609000,"text":"And it's one of the difficult things"},{"time":611000,"text":"is that when people have preconceptions of how it all works,"},{"time":613000,"text":"it's quite difficult to shift those."},{"time":616000,"text":"So we're not empty vessels; the mental models that we have"},{"time":620000,"text":"as children persist into adulthood."},{"time":622000,"text":"Poor teaching actually does more harm than good."},{"time":624000,"text":"In this country and in Britain, magnetism is understood better"},{"time":628000,"text":"by children before they've been to school than afterwards, OK?"},{"time":631000,"text":"Same for gravity, two concepts, so it's -- which is quite humbling,"},{"time":635000,"text":"as a, you know, if you're a teacher, and you look before and after,"},{"time":638000,"text":"that's quite worrying. They do worse in tests afterwards, after the teaching."},{"time":642000,"text":"And we collude. We design tests,"},{"time":644000,"text":"or at least in Britain, so that people pass them. Right?"},{"time":647000,"text":"And governments do very well. They pat themselves on the back."},{"time":650000,"text":"OK? We collude, and actually if you --"},{"time":654000,"text":"if someone had designed a test for me"},{"time":656000,"text":"when I was doing my biology exams,"},{"time":658000,"text":"to really understand, to see whether I'd understood"},{"time":660000,"text":"more than just kind of putting starch and iodine together"},{"time":662000,"text":"and seeing it go blue,"},{"time":664000,"text":"and really understood that plants took their mass out of the air,"},{"time":667000,"text":"then I might have done better at science."},{"time":672000,"text":"So the most important thing is to get people to articulate their models."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677000,"text":"Your homework is -- you know, how does an aircraft's wing create lift?"},{"time":682000,"text":"An obvious question, and you'll have an answer now in your heads."},{"time":686000,"text":"And the second question to that then is,"},{"time":689000,"text":"ensure you've explained how it is that planes can fly upside down."},{"time":693000,"text":"Ah ha, right. Second question is, why is the sea blue? All right?"},{"time":697000,"text":"And you've all got an idea in your head of the answer."},{"time":701000,"text":"So, why is it blue on cloudy days? Ah, see."},{"time":705000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":708000,"text":"I've always wanted to say that in this country."},{"time":710000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":712000,"text":"Finally, my plea to you is to allow yourselves, and your children,"},{"time":716000,"text":"and anyone you know, to kind of fiddle with stuff,"},{"time":719000,"text":"because it's by fiddling with things that you, you know,"},{"time":721000,"text":"you complement your other learning. It's not a replacement,"},{"time":723000,"text":"it's just part of learning that's important."},{"time":726000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":727000,"text":"Now -- oh, oh yeah, go on then, go on."},{"time":730000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}